<common_false_positive_patterns>
REJECT if you observe:
- Client-side template (Angular, Vue, React)
- Template strings reflected literally
- Sandbox prevents dangerous access
- Only string interpolation, no objects
- Server-side but no dangerous primitives
</common_false_positive_patterns>
